<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77529bbb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410ff–6"><num value="410ff–6">§ 410ff–6.</num><heading> Entrance or admission fees prohibited</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no fees shall be charged for entrance or admission to the park.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77529bbc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/199/tII/s207">Pub. L. 96–199, title II, § 207</ref>, <date date="1980-03-05">Mar. 5, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/77">94 Stat. 77</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
